name: NCDistrict
tweet: We will begin accepting appointments for the Covid, booster, and Seasonal Flu vaccines for all residents of NCDHD Counties during normal business hours. Call your local health department to obtain an appointment, walk-ins will be welcome, please bring your COVID vaccination card.  https://t.co/HMJEpM1Bso

tweet: North Central District is offering a Covid-19 mass vaccination clinic on Thursday 9/30/2021 from 2-7pm. This clinic will be held at 615 11th Street, Shelbyville, KY 40065.  https://t.co/JACiMYn74M #NCDHD  https://t.co/Ufgxt8KzX6

name: NCDistrict
tweet: We are reactivating our COVID Hotline due to the high level of COVID cases in our area. If you have any COVID-related questions, please call our hotline at (502) 390-2600, which operates M-F, 8am-4:30pm. The best way to find out the most up-to-date information, related to COVID.

name: NCDistrict
tweet: North Central District is refocusing our efforts towards COVID-19 and reducing many of the routine services we provide. The clinic will continue to provide WIC and immunizations.

name: NCDistrict
tweet: NCDHD has developed a partnership with Bluewater Labs to provide COVID-19 testing for Spencer County. Bluewater Labs will begin testing at the Spencer County Board of Education on 9/7/2021.  Additional sites, coming sometime later in September in our other counties. #ncdhd  https://t.co/tQ2ro2P1NA
